# Workflow: Fundraising Readiness

**Command:** `/workflow fundraise-ready`  
**Agents:** All 7 C-Suite + FP&A, Sales Ops, People Ops

## Purpose
Prepares the company for a fundraising process — data room, narrative, diligence preparation, and investor targeting strategy.

## Phases
1. **Data Room Prep** (management) — FP&A builds financial model and historical financials; Sales Ops builds revenue metrics package; People Ops builds org chart and team bios
2. **Narrative Development** (C-Suite) — each function contributes their element of the company story
3. **Diligence Prep** — each agent identifies the 3 hardest investor questions in their domain and prepares honest answers
4. **Investor Narrative Integration** — CEO produces the integrated pitch and investor targeting strategy

**Output:** Data room checklist, pitch narrative, diligence risk register, hard questions prep sheet, investor targeting criteria

