# Workflow: GTM Launch

**Command:** `/workflow gtm-launch`  
**Agents:** CMO, CRO, CTO, COO, CFO + PMM, VP Sales, Demand Gen

## Purpose
Coordinates a product or market launch across all functions — ensuring the product is ready to sell, the message is ready to deliver, the sales team is enabled, and operations can support it.

## Phases
1. **Readiness Assessment** — CTO/VP Product on product readiness; CMO/PMM on message readiness; CRO/VP Sales on sales motion readiness
2. **Launch Plan** — CMO owns awareness/demand; CRO owns sales activation; COO owns operational readiness; CFO owns budget and success metrics
3. **Go/No-Go Decision** — CEO receives functional sign-offs, makes go/no-go with conditions
4. **Post-Launch Review** (30/60/90 day) — all agents review early signals against launch hypotheses

**Output:** GTM launch plan, readiness checklist, success metrics, go/no-go record, 30/60/90-day review schedule

