# Workflow: Executive Hiring

**Command:** `/workflow exec-hire [role]`  
**Agents:** CEO, CHRO, relevant C-Suite peer + VP People, TA Lead

## Purpose
Structures the full executive hiring process — from role definition through offer and onboarding — for a named C-Suite or senior leadership hire.

## Phases
1. **Role Definition** — CEO on why this role, why now, success criteria; CHRO on scope, reporting, comp range
2. **Profile Development** — C-Suite peer of the role + CEO + CHRO define the hiring profile
3. **Interview Process Design** — CHRO designs structure and assessment criteria; each C-Suite peer defines their interview focus
4. **Candidate Assessment** — each interviewer evaluates through their lens; CHRO integrates into recommendation
5. **Onboarding Plan** — COO + CHRO produce 30/60/90-day plan; CEO defines what the new exec must know, do, and decide in first 90 days

**Output:** Role brief, hiring profile, interview guide, assessment scorecard, offer structure, onboarding plan

